2. Cyzicenis: they had failed to complete a chapel (ἡρῷον), which they had commenced to Augustus, and had imprisoned some Romans (Dio, LVII. 24).

3. bello Mithridatis: this is the siege of Cyzicus mentioned by Cic- ero in his oration for the Manilian law (8. 2o); they had forfeited their privileges once before, in the reign of Augustus, but they had been after- wards restored.

4. Vibium Serenum: of course, the son (28. 1.).
